foliation.p: The manuscript is provided with a foliation from 1-43 and a number of columns from 1-170.

condition.p: The manuscript is fragmentary. Of fol. 1 only the inner half is extant and the lower part is also cut away. Fol. 2 and 43 are also damaged by cutting. Some of the outer margin of fol. 5 has been cut away, and several leaves have small holes and stains.

layout.p: The manuscript is written in double columns with 37 or 38 lines per column. A few exceptions of 36 or 39 lines per column occur. Rubrics in red. Majuscules occur in red, blue, violet and green. Some of the majuscules have a red flourishing.

additions.p:
Religious notes:
10r Gudz nad og fridur sie med idur godvr
22r gud ueri med yfur siraa þ
Personal names:
9v oddur þorsteinns hefur skrifad a bokina
25v bauduar finnz son
27r eg einar Þorbiarnar son hefi lesit þesa bok ut þackar ec ydur firi
landid lanid
42v hamingiunar heppinkior hlioti vm æfi alla Oddü jonsson med eiginn hand.
Partly illegible notes ar found on ff. 12v, 18v, 26v and 34v.

binding.p: The manuscript is bound in a modern standard half binding from 1970.

list.item: An AM-slip pasted on 1r reads: Þetta er prologus framan firer Olafs sgu Helga. og byriast ä þeim ordum: Ari prestr hinn frodi. Synest þetta ad vera fyrri dalkr sidunnar, og vantar nedan vid 5. Sidari dalkur sidunnar er burtu, og fyrri dalkurinn af pagina libri 2da. Hefr so prologus vered ä 3. dalkum. og conseqventer älika girdur sem sä er stendr i Olafs sgu þeirre er eg feck fra Bæ ä Raudasande. Þetta hefi eg feinged ur drum stad enn sialfa bokina.
An AM-slip pasted between ff. 36 and 37 (concerning fol. 37) reads: Þetta blad hefi eg feinged sier i lage. Eg ætla þad heyri hier inn.

origin.p: The manuscript is written in Iceland in the fourteenth century.

custEvent.p: From the 28th of February to the fourteenth of September 1970, the manuscript was bound in a modern standard half binding by Birgitte Dall.
